==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incarnadine
<hw>In*car"na*dine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>incarnadin</ets>, It. <ets>incarnatino</ets>; L. pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>caro</ets>, <ets>carnis</ets>, flesh. Cf.
<er>Carnation</er>, <er>Incarnate</er>.]</ety> <def>Flesh-colored; of a
carnation or pale red color.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Lovelace.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incarnadine</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Incarnadine
<hw>In*car"na*dine</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To dye red or
crimson.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Will all great Neptune's ocean wash this blood⟦br⟧
Clean from my hand? No; this my hand will rather⟦br⟧
The multitudinous seas <qex>incarnadine</qex>,⟦br⟧
Making the green one red.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incarnate</ent>⟦br⟧
